https://intellipaat.com/tutorial/angular-6-tutorial/(tutorial)


->To install angular 6 needed environment:
1.Nodejs(min 6.0 or above)
2.Npm:(->npm set proxy http://kolla.saisudha:password@gtpproxy.mphasis.com:8080 
                                        (or)
        npm set https-proxy http://kolla.saisudha:password@gtpproxy.mphasis.com:8080
       ->npm config set strict-ssl false -g)
3.Angular cli(7.3.8 version):(->npm i -g @angular/cli@7.3.8
                              ->[ng -v] to see installed or not)
4.IDE for code(visual studio code)

->ng --version (or) ng v : for angular cli version information.
->npm -v for version of npm.

->Angular is used for single page applications(SPA).
->Uses typescript or Dart and then converts it into javascript(Transpilation(converting from 1 source code to another)).

->creating project:
  ng new projectname
  ng build : To compile your Angular project into an output directory
  ng serve --open (or) ng s --o : This command is used when you want to open your project in a web browser.
  
->npm i for install
  npm update for updating
  npm u for uninstall
  npm u -g @angular/cli
  npm cache clean
  npm i -g @angular/cli : to install angular/cli
  npm u package@version
  
->ng g c componentname for creating a component
  ng g p pipename for creating pipe
  ng g service servicename for creating service
  ng g service services/users/users: (example) ==> services->users.
  
->ng serve -port 4201 : When we use serve command without specifying the port like in previous command, the project runs on 4200 port 
    by default. This command is used when we want to run the project on a specified port. (In this case, port 4201)
 
 ->nf config : To retrieve or send Angular configuration values in angular.json file
   ng run ProjectName : To run the project with an optional custom builder
   ng generate or ng g : This helps in adding elements to your applications
   ng test : This command runs unit tests in your projects
    
  
